  "texts": [
    "Distinct from the existing multi-actor approaches [27] [28] [29], the approach for extracting key-insights from scientific articles merges the unique viewpoints from disparate models.",
    "Consequently, such customary solutions as weight updating 27 and expert routing 29 prove ineffective for this task.",
    "Our approach addresses this by finetuning a specialized actor tasked with integrating and summarizing information from other actors.",
    "While this method may not achieve the execution efficiency of expert routing techniques, it significantly enhances the accuracy of key-insights extraction, ensuring maximal fidelity to the source article.",
    "The results of this study also suggest an insight: the inherent abilities of the original LLMs are more important than the enhancements brought about by fine-tuning."
  ],
